a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/electrify-americas-charging-network-will-support-teslas-nacs-connector-by-2025-185317197.html">Electrify America 充电器</a>中添加 NACS 之外，尚未承诺这一想法。在美国， <a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/ford-ev-drivers-will-get-access-to-12000-north-american-tesla-superchargers-next-spring-221752191.html">福特</a>、 <a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/gm-ev-owners-will-gain-access-to-tesla-superchargers-in-2024-002123436.html">通用汽车</a>和<a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/rivian-owners-will-be-able-to-use-tesla-superchargers-starting-in-2024-141546633.html">Rivian 等</a>公司已承诺支持特斯拉的技术。移动协会 SAE 正在<a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/the-sae-is-creating-a-standardized-version-of-teslas-ev-charging-plug-175233691.html">生产该插头的标准化版本</a>，可以帮助其他供应商使用该格式。</p><p>这不是一个全球性的转变，与福特和通用汽车等价格更实惠的品牌相比，梅赛德斯的高端市场将限制其影响力。不过，转向 NACS 增加了大众汽车和其他仍在北美使用 CCS 的竞争对手的压力。他们面临着继续使用不太常见的电动汽车插头的风险，这可能会损害长途驾驶，进而影响汽车销售。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/mercedes-will-use-teslas-ev-charging-standard-on-north-american-cars-161547427.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/mercedes-will-use-teslas-ev-charging-standard-on-north-american-cars-161547427.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 748e1e64-9cb3-4550-85dd-a79f3263d60c</guid><dc:creator>乔恩·芬加斯</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Fri, 07 Jul 2023 17:15:47 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1688747460</ingested><modified> 2023-07-07T16:31:04+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Automotive Industry]]></category><category><![CDATA[Autos]]></category><category><![CDATA[Transportation]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></c